The paper discusses a system for data ingestion and preprocessing, which is a common problem in database systems. Therefore, cs.DB (Database) is the most likely sub-category. The system also involves distributed and fault-tolerant processing, which suggests that it may also fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The use of optimization techniques and query plans is reminiscent of query processing, which is a topic in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the use of a declarative language for specifying ingestion plans, which is a topic in cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper presents experimental results, which suggests that it may also fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
